Description: Typical range for pulsed Nd:YAG lasers in polymer cleaning to avoid thermal damage; starting at 30W for PMMA surface preparation. Max safe ~100W before melting (PMMA melting point ~160°C). Source: Manufacturer specs from IPG Photonics and Adapt Laser Systems for delicate substrates.
Larger spot for gentle surface treatment
Lower frequency to prevent thermal damage
Short pulses for minimal thermal impact
Fast scanning to reduce heat accumulation
Multiple gentle passes for gradual cleaning
